def: Any plant which habitually breaks away from its roots in theautumn, and is driven by the wind, as a light, rolling mass, over thefields and prairies; as witch grass, wild indigo, Amarantus albus,etc.
A drowning of many persons at once, -- a method of executionpracticed at Nantes in France during the Reign of Terror, by JeanBaptiste Carrier.
A genus of Hymenoptera including the common wasps and hornets.

To render more intense; as, to intensify heat or cold; tointensify colors; to intensify a photographic negative; to intensifyanimosity. Bacon.How piercing is the sting of pride By want embittered andintensified. Longfellow.
The fore part of the deck, having a bulkhead athwart ships highenough to prevent water which enters the hawse holes from runningover it.
To hold or value too highly; to estimate at too dear a rate.[Obs.] Shak.
One in genesis; resulting from one process of formation; --used of a mountain range. Dana.
